nd concert-promotion, the introduction of the long-playing record, the suburbanization of Los Angeles, the Civil Rights movement, the "British invasion" and the rise of electronic instruments. This groundbreaking book deepens our appreciation of this music by identifying many of the developments outside of jazz itself that contributed most to its texture, complexity, and growth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJazzxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Jazz.2bisacsh  a20th century america.  a20th century music.  aamerican federation of music.  aamerican history.  abooks for music lovers.  acalifornia history.  acivil rights movement.  aculture of jazz.  adiscussion books.  aeducational books.  aevolution of music.  aevolution of radio.  ajazz and society.  ajazz history.  amusic criticism.  amusic history.  amusic studies.  amusic.  amusicians.  anonfiction books.  aperforming arts.  apolitics and music.  apost war art.  apost war culture.  aradio history.  arise of los angeles.  asocial history of america.  athe anatomy of music.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026878440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095398740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953987423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953987/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY